Here is the Java code to sum 1 to 10:

```java
public class SumOfNumbers {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int sum = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
            sum += i;
        }
        System.out.println("The sum of 1 to 10 is: " + sum);
    }
}
```

In this code, we first initialize a variable `sum` to 0. We then use a `for` loop to iterate from 1 to 10. Inside the loop, we add each number to the `sum` variable. Finally, we print out the sum using the `System.out.println()` method.
